{meta: title A Mother's Way}
{meta: artist Foster and Allen}
{meta: composer Reg Keating}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]It's just a mother's [F]way  [G7]to worry through the [C]day
[F]Bout every little thing like falling off a [G7]swing
[C]When you are out at play
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[F]The years [G7]slide quickly by  the summers seem to [C]fly
[F]And then you move along you break out on your [G7]own
[C]But you don't see her cry
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[F]For a while she hides behind a smile
[G7]But then her eyes reveal she worries still [C]today
[F]Take her hand show her you understand
[G7]A little tenderness will go a long long [C]way
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[F]And now the [G7]years have flown  she's sitting all [C]alone
[F]With all her photographs and memories of the [G7]past
[C]She's glad when you come home
{end_of_verse}

